I am building a JavaScript application for a sumo wrestling game. In this game, players select a wrestler for each basho in a wave. I need to build a 'Pick' object that represents a pick made by a player. It should contain the wrestler's name and potentially other relevant details.

ChatGPT
Sure! I can help you with that. In JavaScript, you can define an object using either object literals or constructor functions. Here's an example of how you can create a 'Pick' object for your sumo wrestling game:

```javascript
// Using object literals
const pick = {
  wrestlerName: '',
  // You can add more properties relevant to the pick if needed
};

// Using a constructor function
function Pick(wrestlerName) {
  this.wrestlerName = wrestlerName;
  // You can add more properties relevant to the pick if needed
}

// Usage
const myPick = new Pick('Sumo Wrestler 1');
console.log(myPick.wrestlerName); // Output: Sumo Wrestler 1
```

In the above code, the Pick object represents a pick made by a player. It has a wrestlerName property to store the name of the wrestler selected by the player. You can add additional properties to the object as needed, such as waveNumber or bashoNumber to keep track of the specific wave or basho for which the pick is made.

You can create a new instance of the Pick object using either object literals (the first example) or constructor functions (the second example). In both cases, you can assign the wrestler's name to the wrestlerName property.

